<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n15013d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n15" href="#n15013d">N15 (VI.D.2)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n15all.htm#n15013d"> 13(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> padovana</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> onde si fond&ograve; il primo regno d&apos;Assiria nella gente caldea; e ne rest&ograve; Caldeo per Erudito, come ne&apos; tempi barbari a noi vicini in Italia, <mark><i>Padovano</i></mark> per Letterato <br><font color="green">[Hence the first kingdom of Assyria was founded by the Chaldean race, from which the word &lsquo;Chaldean&rsquo; survived as a synonym for &lsquo;erudite&rsquo;, just as in the barbaric times close to us, the word &lsquo;<mark>Paduan</mark>&rsquo; survived for &lsquo;learned&rsquo;.]</font> <small> Giovanni Battista Vico, <a name="VICO2" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#VICO2"><cite title="source">Principes de la philosophe de l'histoire</cite></a> (edition unknown) Book II, Ch. LVII</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c15189d" href="c15all.htm#c15189d">VI.C.15:189(d)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
